# Richardson, Chris - [Mid Term Program]

print ("Planet Express Delivery Time Calculator")

planetone = input("What is the name of the planet?")
parsecsone = input ("How many parsecs away?")
packagesone = input ("How many packages?")
tonsone = input ("How many tons does each package weigh?")

parsecsone = float(parsecsone)
tonsone = float(tonsone)
packagesone = int(packagesone)

timeone = (tonsone + parsecsone)
timeone = float (timeone)
  
cargoweightone = (tonsone * packagesone)
cargoweightone = float(cargoweightone)
  
tripone = (cargoweightone * parsecsone + parsecsone)
tripone = float(tripone)
  
totaltripone = (tripone + parsecsone)
totaltripone = float(totaltripone)




isplanetone = str("Robot Planet")

#Proer Validation showing Error messages


if (tonsone < 0):
  print ("Error: The package weight", tonsone, "is too light.")
  

elif (packagesone == 0):
  print ("Error: the ship must carry at least one package.")
  

elif (parsecsone < 1):
  print (planetone, "must be one or more parsecs away.")

  # Print Commands
  
elif (packagesone > 10 and packagesone % 2):
  packagestwo = packagesone + 1
  cargoweighttwo = (tonsone * packagestwo)
  cargoweighttwo = float (cargoweighttwo)
  triptwo =(cargoweighttwo * parsecsone + parsecsone)
  triptwo = float(triptwo)
  totaltriptwo =(triptwo + parsecsone)
  totaltriptwo = float (totaltriptwo)
  print ("Warning: Adjsuting package count to", packagestwo)
  print ("The total cargo weight is", cargoweighttwo, "ton(s).")
  print ("The trip to", planetone, "will take", triptwo, " minutes.")
  print ("The trip back to Earth will take", parsecsone, "minutes.")
  print ("The total trip time is ", totaltriptwo, "minutes.")
  
  
else: 
  print ("The total cargo weight is", cargoweightone, "ton(s).")
  print ("The trip to", planetone, "will take", tripone, " minutes.")
  print ("The trip back to Earth will take", parsecsone, "minutes.")
  print ("The total trip time is ", totaltripone, "minutes.") 
  

      
if (planetone == isplanetone):
  print ("Also, Bender is great!")
